Description:
Expressions of interest closing on Wednesday 21 March
Urban Lifestyle, Culture and Convenience To Spare.
This first floor residence offers a spacious open plan living area with a generous North facing terrace, and a leafy outlook, perfect for entertaining. Features modern kitchen with stone bench top, dishwasher, European cooking appliances and ample cupboard space. Other highlights include central bathroom, separate laundry area, secure lock up storage unit and heating and cooling. Located within one of Collingwood's best cafe districts, with Smith & Gertrude Streets only minutes away. This unique apartment is securely leased at $1673 PCM. Only 15 residences in this boutique building with a cafe on the ground level. In conjunction with Selling Homes Melbourne. Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday 21 March , if not sold prior.

Description:
Great space & central location - double the excitement
A double-storey Victorian at the East Melbourne-end of Collingwood is a rarity and what's more remarkable is that just nearby are a stack of cafes, bars and boutiques plus the MCG, city trains, Fitzroy Gardens and the Yarra. This incredibly central home is an absolute gem. Superbly laid out and appointed for secluded and spacious city-fringe living, this 3 bedroom residence framed by high ceilings and polished floorboards features living and dining areas flowing to landscaped garden surroundings with decking, large kitchen including stainless-steel appliances and great storage, stylish bathroom with clawfoot bath, powder room, laundry, double-glazed main bedroom with BIR/drawer wall, 2nd bedroom opening to fabulous entertainment deck, gas heating, OFPs and modern lighting.

Description:
Circular symmetries: vast and versatile with CBD views
In the landmark conversion of the Distillery Silos, this ultra-spacious apartment with city and Dandenongs views offers a striking design for CBD-edge living in the heart of the Collingwood warehouse precinct, minutes from Smith Street cafes, transport and East Melbourne parkland. Versatility is the keynote of the design, which encompasses two extremely large circular living/office spaces with balconies, well-equipped kitchen (premium appliances and fittings), three further principal rooms, two bathrooms, powder room and laundry. Entered from a leafy piazza and lift entry, this unique property features ample storage, polished timber floors, split-system air conditioning, secure under cover parking and a lockable storage cage. [Note: zoned Commercial 2]

Description:
Heritage cottage, refurbished with flair
Picture perfect! This freestanding double-fronted Victorian residence with authentic period warmth offers comfortable living now with wonderful potential for further enhancement. Filled with light, it comprises 2 double bedrooms opening from a central hall, a spacious sitting room, large dining room and well-equipped kitchen flowing to a delightful secluded garden, plus an elegant bathroom with period fittings and concealed laundry. Close to Smith Street shops, local cafes and Queens Parade, this captivating home with side access to Charlotte Street features waxed hardwood floors, Baltic detail, handcrafted cabinetry, gas heating, split-system air conditioning and side access to bike storage. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Under Instructions from the Mortgagee
Just over 2 years old and built on the Yorkshire Brewery site right in the heart of Collingwood, is this luxurious 10th floor apartment with stunning city views and loads of extra amenities including share cars and bikes, dining room, gymnasium and a roof top BBQ area. Featuring 2 bedrooms both with Built In robes, the main is huge with a great study nook and access to its very own balcony. A large open plan incorporates the galley style designer kitchen which features stone bench tops, glass splash back and stainless steel European appliances with gas cooking. Enjoy the space of living/dining and from the adjoining central balcony, revel in those amazing city views. Other features include a central bathroom with large shower and Euro laundry, timber flooring, split system, pull out pantry, extra storage, NBN ready, secure entry into the building, video intercom for any arrivals and a basement car space, not that you will need it being only approx. 2.5 km to the CBD. Within walking distance to the chic lifestyle of Smith and Brunswick Streets and to surrounding cafes, retail outlets, and public transport, you will certainly enjoy the locale that trendy Collingwood has to offer.

Description:
Clearly a one of a kind conversion
From warehouse origins to refined residential spaces, this unique inner city sanctuary delivers spectacular dimensions beneath a soaring 5m ceiling that enhances the sense of space and volume while northern light keeps everything constantly bright. Living and dining areas featuring a gas fire-place and reverse cycle central heating/cooling flow to a large, low-maintenance courtyard oasis that provides an enticing backdrop for a contemporary kitchen featuring stone benches and a fully fitted walk-in pantry. The alluring accommodation of three bedrooms and two bathrooms includes a luxurious main bedroom, its own upstairs zone accompanied by a sunny, north facing terrace, fitted walk-in robes and a superb double shower ensuite. Automatic blinds, a city view, bespoke back-lit wall art, mains gas BBQ and a double garage with storage further enhance an ideally situated address that remains perfectly private behind original factory walls with intercom entrance and back to base security.

Description:
Bold and boutique warehouse living
In Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct, this fabulous first-floor apartment delivers a lifestyle/investment of quality and class with its impressive inclusions, secure surrounds and premier location with the best of inner-Melbourne at your fingertips. Warehouse appeal with contemporary flair, the apartment's chic interior comprises a double bedroom (BIRs) and stylish central bathroom, light-filled open living/dining area out to a full-width undercover terrace. Add to this a Smeg-equipped kitchen with stone benches and timber-top breakfast bar, plus split-system a/c, polished concrete floors, secure entry foyer and lower-level parking space. Positioned to perfection, Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, city-bound trams are all within walking distance.

Bold and beautiful inner-city living
Cutting-edge style with secure boutique surrounds, this 3rd-floor apartment delivers an inspired concept of inner-urban lifestyle excellence amid historic local surrounds and moments from the buzz of Smith Street. As-new interior showcases main bedroom and study/2nd bedroom (both with BIRs) and sleek central bathroom, open-design living/dining area leading out to a sunny bluestone-paved terrace. Description:
The Ultimate Urban Lifestyle
Architect designed with an eye on community living this two bedroom two bathroom designer apartment, part of Collingwood's historic Foy and Gibson complex, boasts excellent entry to a trendy locale. And what a locale, with everything Smith Street is famous for at your door, from cafes, bars and restaurants, to specialty shopping, supermarkets and trams it delivers the best of inner-city living. Designed with a strong sense of community this modern apartment complex boasts a communal library space, range of gardens including Indigenous and herb gardens together with a European Garden incorporating an outdoor entertaining space, it provides a serene and inclusive lifestyle. Clean modern lines are paired with high-end luxe finishes to deliver a sophisticated living space showcasing a sleek Miele equipped Caesarstone kitchen featuring smoky mirrored splashbacks, open shelving and moveable island/breakfast bar that spills to a spacious balcony extending the living space and providing a private outdoor space to enjoy. Double bedroom with BIR's are each complemented by luxuriously fitted bathrooms featuring oversized showers, the master with a neat study nook. Add to this a Euro laundry secure entry, heating/cooling and car space, positioned in a true lifestyle locale it makes the ideal inner-urban pad or savvy addition to any investment portfolio.
Alexkarbon Real Estate
122 Errol Street, North Melbourne VIC 3051

Islington Silos

Description:
Generously expansive apartment in prime Collingwood location
Set next to the trendy Fitzroy food and entertainment district, this extensive 1 bedroom apartment has much to offer. Featuring an open plan living and dining area that gives you unlimited access to sunlight and fresh air from the balcony. The kitchen is equipped with stainless steel stovetop including a dishwasher and oven plus ample storage. A separate laundry is neatly tucked away for personal convenience.
The prime location offers quick access to Hodgson Street tram stop and Smith Street bus stop with Woolworths situated just across the street. Indulge in nearby culinary selections including Gelato Messina and Saint Crispin or explore the vast selections of handmade artworks and jewelry at in.cube8r within minutes walking distance. Fitzroy Primary School, Collingwood English School and Melbourne Girl's College can also be found within the vicinity.

Historic Distillery Conversion
Exclusive Block of Only 12

Top floor, top class
This top floor east facing apartment is part of the boutique "Haus" development designed by Stoll-Long Architects. Comprising 2 bedrooms both with BIRs, modern kitchen, designer finishes, high ceilings throughout, heating/cooling, ample storage, security entry, lift access and OSP with storage locker. Moments from Smith Streets vibrant cafe & restaurant precinct, plus Gertrude, Victorian & Brunswick Streets, with ample public transport, MCG, East Melbourne and CBD close by.

Description:
Secluded contemporary style, exclusive cafe precinct living
Filled with northern light, this elegant ground floor apartment in the acclaimed Elenberg Fraser-designed Oxley development offers CBD-edge living at its finest. A must-see opportunity for professionals and smart investors, this stylish residence comprises one double bedroom (BIRs) and adjoining study/home office, sleek bathroom with walk-in shower and European laundry, and an open plan living/dining area featuring floor-to-ceiling double glazed windows flowing to a bright full-width terrace. This tranquil apartment features a well-appointed kitchen, heating and cooling, intercom and secure entry, NBN connection, plus lift access to an undercover parking space and storage cage. Moments from city-bound trams and Smith Street's renowned cafe culture, here is an idyllic inner-city lifestyle opportunity, including access to landscaped gardens, shared outdoor entertaining spaces and a rooftop swimming pool.

Description:
From brewery to brilliant.
The transition from the evocative industrial origins of the Yorkshire Brewery precinct to the residential brilliance of a city edge address is perfectly illustrated by this highly desirable dual level townhouse. A traditional period façade, instantly reflective of its Victorian era, creates an elegant introduction to superb spaces including a downstairs living and dining area framed by stylish timber floors and handsome ceiling beams. An open plan kitchen featuring marble benches, integrated storage, concealed fridge and Miele appliances makes a memorable contribution to these perfectly private dimensions while alluring accommodation defines the upper level. Two bedrooms and two bathrooms, including a main bedroom with walk in robes to a seductive ensuite, are irresistibly appealing. The downstairs powder room, excellent storage and secure garaging for two cars further complement inner city environs offering a gym, library and barbeque deck.
